    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> April 2026</p>

    <p>Headius Enterprises ("we", "us", "our") operates the website headius.com. This policy describes what personal data we collect, how we use it, and what rights you have regarding that data.</p>

    <h2>What We Collect</h2>

    <h3>Contact Enquiries</h3>
    <p>If you contact us via email at <a href="mailto:support@headius.com">support@headius.com</a> or through our contact form (which opens your email client to send the message), we collect the information you provide — typically your name, email address, and the content of your message. We use this information solely to respond to your enquiry. We do not add you to any mailing list unless you explicitly request it.</p>

    <h3>Subscription Payments</h3>
    <p>If you purchase a support subscription, payment is processed by <a href="https://stripe.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stripe</a>. We do not store your credit card number or payment details on our servers. Stripe collects and processes your payment information in accordance with their <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h2>Cookies and Local Storage</h2>

    <p>This site does not set any first-party cookies. We do not use analytics, tracking pixels, or advertising scripts.</p>

    <p>We store the following preferences in your browser's local storage. These are not cookies and are not transmitted to any server:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>headius-consent</strong> — records which third-party providers you have consented to load (e.g., YouTube, Google, Reddit).</li>
      <li><strong>headius-theme</strong> — records your preferred colour theme (dark, light, or high contrast).</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

