    <p>When you consent to load YouTube videos, we use youtube-nocookie.com (YouTube's privacy-enhanced mode) to minimise tracking. When you consent to load an embedded Reddit discussion, Reddit may set cookies on your device in accordance with their privacy policy.</p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Contact correspondence:</strong> We retain emails and messages for as long as they remain relevant to our business relationship.</li>
      <li><strong>Payment records:</strong> Transaction records are retained as required by applicable tax and accounting regulations.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>

    <p>Regardless of your location, you may:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you</li>
      <li><strong>Correct</strong> any inaccurate data</li>
      <li><strong>Delete</strong> your data</li>
      <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing of your data</li>
      <li><strong>Request a copy</strong> of your data in a portable format</li>
    </ul>

    <p>If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA) or United Kingdom, these rights are guaranteed under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR). If you are in California, the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) provides similar protections.</p>

    <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:support@headius.com">support@headius.com</a>.</p>

    <h2>Children</h2>

    <p>This site is not directed at children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children.</p>

    <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>

    <p>If we make changes to this policy, we will update the date at the top of this page.</p>

